before%20being%20rebranded%20as%20%E2%80%98Ambico%20Ice%20Factory%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%202019%2C%20when%20Malik%20first%20set%20sight%20on%20the%20building%2C%20he%20acquired%20it%20but%20with%20no%20plans%20to%20renovate%20or%20repurpose%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F366166%2Fcossimbazar-palace-of-roys-rajbari-murshidabad-west-bengal-ancestral-palaces-heritage-hotel%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epiece%20of%20history%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20banyan%20tree%2C%20however%2C%20would%20etch%20an%20image%20in%20Malik%E2%80%99s%20mind%20that%20would%20eventually%20become%20the%20seed%20that%20would%20reinvigorate%20the%20establishment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAt%20the%20time%2C%20I%20had%20no%20idea%2C%20whatsoever%2C%20of%20either%20acquiring%20such%20a%20space%20or%20wanting%20to%20do%20something%20with%20it.%20But%20the%20image%20of%20the%20banyan%20tree%20stayed%20with%20me%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20recalls.%20A%20few%20months%20later%2C%20Malik%20found%20himself%20saying%20a%20%E2%80%98yes%E2%80%99%20to%20the%20project%2C%20joined%20by%20Abhijit%20Mehta%2C%20Arjun%20Malik%2C%20and%20Amrita%20Malik.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2Fsustainable-architecture-2-1726747206.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Kamal%20Malik%20has%20over%20five%20decades%20of%20experience%20in%20architectural%20projects%20which%20have%20kept%20sustainability%20at%20the%20fore%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2Fsustainable-architecture-2-1726747206.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2Fsustainable-architecture-2-1726747206-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fupl